  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (residual-risk gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A known limitation regarding turbulence-model sensitivity at low-flow edge cases is acknowledged in the validation narrative; however, no documented rationale explains why the residual risk associated with this limitation is acceptable for the specific COU.",
