    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-hemolysis-validation-primary",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary hemolysis index validation against FDA benchmark experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against published FDA generic centrifugal pump experimental measurements across 5 operating points. Predicted NIH values fell within 15% of experimental measurements at 4 of 5 operating points. At the lowest flow rate condition (2 L/min, 3500 RPM), the SST k-omega turbulence model underestimated shear stress in the volute region by approximately 22%, leading to underprediction of NIH. This edge case is noted as a known limitation of the turbulence model formulation under transitional flow regimes. The limitation is flagged per standard practice for CFD hemolysis assessments."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-mesh-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error quantification",
      "description": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted using meshes of 2.1M, 5.8M, and 14.2M cells. Grid convergence index (GCI) for the NIH quantity of interest was computed as 3.2% on the fine mesh, meeting the required discretization error threshold of 5% for MRL 2. Iterative convergence was confirmed with residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations."
    },
