    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-cpb-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for the Morrison COU1 CFD hemolysis model is accepted at Model Risk Level 2. All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per MRL 2 requirements. A known limitation exists regarding turbulence model underprediction at the 2 L/min low-flow edge case, where NIH deviation exceeds the 20% threshold. This limitation is consistent with published CFD hemolysis literature and is considered acceptable per standard practice in the field. The primary operating envelope relevant to worst-case hemolysis identification is adequately validated. The model is accepted for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
